<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="KR1h0004-en-ff4e6933" type="transl"><teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Analects of Confucius.A Philosophical Translation</title><editor role="translator">Ames and Rosemont 1998</editor></titleStmt><publicationStmt><ab>published electronically as part of the TLS project at https://hxwd.org</ab><availability status="4">The copyright status of this work is unclear</availability></publicationStmt><sourceDesc><bibl><title>The Analects of Confucius.A Philosophical Translation</title>New York 1998</bibl><ab>Translation of <bibl corresp="#KR1h0004"><title xml:lang="och">論語</title></bibl> into <lang xml:lang="en">English</lang>.</ab></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><creation resp="#CH">Initially created: <date>2023-10-19T04:42:29.13+09:00</date> by CH</creation></profileDesc></teiHeader><text><body><div><head>Translated parts</head><p xml:id="KR1h0004-start"><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-1a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:43:46.872+09:00">The Master said:</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-1a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T17:11:12.821+09:00">“Having studied,1 to then repeatedly apply what you have learned—</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-1a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-23T22:34:45.432+09:00">is this not a source of pleasure?</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-1a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-23T22:35:00.422+09:00">To have friends come from distant quarters2—</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-1a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T17:13:13.698+09:00">is this not a source of enjoyment?</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-1a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-23T22:35:17.261+09:00">To go unacknowledged by others without harboring frustration—</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-2a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:44:24.874+09:00">is this not the markof an exemplary person (junzi )?</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-2a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:44:48.503+09:00">Master You3 said:</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-2a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-23T22:35:35.18+09:00">“It is a rare thing for someonewho has a sense of 􀉹lial and fraternal responsibility (xiaodi ) to have a taste for defying authority.</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-2a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-23T22:35:48.901+09:00"> And it is unheard of for those who have no taste for defying authority to be keen on initiating rebellion.</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-2a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-23T22:35:51.792+09:00">Exemplary persons (junzi) concentrate their efforts on the root,</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-2a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-23T22:36:31.39+09:00">for the root having taken hold, the way (dao ) will growtherefrom.</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-2a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:45:51.826+09:00">As for 􀉹lial and fraternal responsibility,</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-3a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:45:52.466+09:00">it is, I suspect, the root of authoritative conduct(ren ).”4</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-3a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:47:13.301+09:00">The Master said:</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-3a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:47:19.327+09:00">“It is a rare thing for glib speechand an insinuating appearance</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-4a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:47:07.465+09:00">to accompanyauthoritative conduct (ren ).”5</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-4a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:47:39.973+09:00">Master Zeng said:</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-4a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:47:46.395+09:00">“Daily I examine my person onthree counts.</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-4a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:47:59.809+09:00">In my undertakings on behalf ofother people, have I failed to do my utmost (zhong)?</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-4a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:48:08.32+09:00">In my interactions with colleagues and friends,have I failed to make good on my word (xin )?</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-5a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:48:10.16+09:00">Inwhat has been passed on to me, have I failed tocarry it into practice?”</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-5a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:48:29.679+09:00">The Master said:</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-5a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:48:47.519+09:00">“The way (dao ) to lead athousand-chariot state</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-5a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:48:57.991+09:00">effectively is to carry outyour o􀉽cial duties respectfully and make good onyour word (xin );</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-5a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:49:04.154+09:00">be frugal in your expendituresand love your peers;</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-6a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:49:04.892+09:00">and put the common peopleto work only at the proper time of year.”6</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-6a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:49:47.88+09:00">The Master said:</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-6a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:50:00.429+09:00">“As a younger brother and son,</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-6a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:50:14.125+09:00">be 􀉹lial (xiao ) at home</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-6a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:50:20.24+09:00"> and deferential (di ) inthe community;</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-6a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:50:35.871+09:00"> be cautious in what you say andthen make good on your word (xin );</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-6a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:50:44.098+09:00"> love themultitude broadly and be intimate with those whoare authoritative in their conduct (ren ).7</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-6a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:50:47.79+09:00"> If in sobehaving you still have energy left,</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-7a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:50:48.789+09:00">use it toimprove yourself through study.”</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-7a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:51:11.655+09:00">Zixia8 said:</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-7a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:51:22.243+09:00">“As for persons who care for charactermuch more than beauty,</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-7a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:51:58.984+09:00">who in serving theirparents are able to exert themselves utterly,</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-7a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:52:07.919+09:00">whogive their whole person in the service of theirruler,</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-7a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:52:14.108+09:00">and who, in interactions with colleagues andfriends, make good on their word (xin )—</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-7a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:52:20.476+09:00">even ifit were said of such persons that they areunschooled,</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-8a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:52:21.083+09:00">I would insist that they are welleducated indeed.”</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-8a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:52:55.505+09:00">The Master said:</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-8a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:53:04.168+09:00">“Exemplary persons (junzi )lacking in gravity would have no dignity.</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-8a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:53:12.917+09:00">Yet intheir studies they are not in􀉻exible.9</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-8a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:53:22.265+09:00">Take doingyour utmost and making good on your word (xin) as your mainstay.</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-8a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:53:31.37+09:00">Do not have as a friendanyone who is not as good as you are.10</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-9a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:53:39.396+09:00">Andwhere you have erred, do not hesitate to mendyour ways.”</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-9a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:54:09.743+09:00">Master Zeng said:</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-9a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:54:18.413+09:00">“Be circumspect in funeraryservices</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-9a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:54:25.68+09:00">and continue sacri􀉹ces to the distantancestors,</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-10a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:54:26.089+09:00">and the virtue (de ) of the commonpeople will thrive.”11</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-10a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:54:52.212+09:00">Ziqin asked Zigong:12</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-10a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:55:00.804+09:00">“When the Master arrives ina particular state</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-10a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-07-22T22:26:21.464+09:00">and needs to learn how it is being governed,</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-10a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:55:39.831+09:00">does he seek out this information</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-10a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:55:43.985+09:00">or is it offered to him?”</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-10a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:55:49.704+09:00">Zigong replied:</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-10a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-07-22T22:26:19.805+09:00">“The Master gets all he needs by being cordial, proper, deferential, frugal, and unassuming.</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-10a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-07-22T22:26:05.217+09:00">Perhaps this way of seeking information</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-11a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-07-22T22:26:03.39+09:00">is somewhat different from how others go about it.”</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-11a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:56:43.81+09:00">The Master said:</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-11a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-07-22T22:25:58.32+09:00">“While a person’s father is still alive,</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-11a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:56:54.921+09:00">observe what he intends;</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-11a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-07-22T22:25:55.947+09:00">when his father dies,</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-11a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:57:25.14+09:00"> observe what he does.13</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-11a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-07-22T22:25:49.757+09:00">A person who for three years refrains from reforming14 the ways(dao ) of his late father</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-12a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-07-22T22:25:40.969+09:00">can be called a filial son(xiao ).”15</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-12a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:58:08.224+09:00">Master You said:</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-12a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-07-22T22:25:26.908+09:00">“Achieving harmony (he ) is the most valuable function of observing ritual propriety (li ).</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-12a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:58:39.291+09:00">In the ways of the Former Kings,</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-12a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:58:52.175+09:00">this achievement of harmony made them elegant,</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-12a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-07-22T22:25:19.696+09:00">and was a guiding standard in all things large and small.</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-12a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:59:04.016+09:00">But when things are not going well,</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-12a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-07-22T22:25:15.894+09:00">to realize harmony just for its own sake</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-12a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-07-22T22:25:11.919+09:00">without regulating the situation through observing ritual propriety</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-13a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:59:26.287+09:00">will not work.”16</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-13a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T04:59:58.272+09:00">Master You said:</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-13a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T05:00:06.263+09:00">“That making good on one’s word(xin ) gets one close to being appropriate (yi )</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-13a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T05:00:13.221+09:00">is because then what one says will bear repeating.</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-13a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-07-22T22:25:05.062+09:00">That being deferential gets one close to observing ritual propriety (li )</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-13a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T05:10:25.465+09:00">is because it keeps disgrace and insult at a distance.</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-13a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-07T13:44:27.329+09:00">Those who are accommodating and do not lose those with whom they</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-14a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T05:01:28.188+09:00">are close are deserving of esteem.”</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-14a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T05:02:26.022+09:00">The Master said:</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-14a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T05:02:36.643+09:00">“In eating, exemplary persons(junzi ) do not look for a full stomach,</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-14a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-07T13:44:27.519+09:00"> nor in their lodgings for comfort and contentment.</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-14a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-07T13:44:38.138+09:00">They are persons of action yet cautious in what they say.</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-14a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T05:03:04.38+09:00">They repair to those who know the way (dao), and 􀉹nd improvement in their company.</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-15a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-07T13:44:48.671+09:00">Suchpersons can indeed be said to have a love of learning (haoxue ).”</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-15a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T05:03:37.417+09:00">Zigong said:</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-15a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-07T13:45:03.99+09:00">“What do you think of the saying: ‘Poor but not inferior;</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-15a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-07T13:45:04.08+09:00">The Master replied:</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-15a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T05:04:17.232+09:00">rich but not superior’?”</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-15a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T05:04:32.428+09:00">“Not bad,</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-15a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-04-07T13:45:15.254+09:00">but not as good as: ‘Poor but enjoying the way (dao );18</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-16a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T05:04:47.005+09:00">rich but lovingritual propriety (li )’ ”</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-16a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T05:05:24.587+09:00">Zigong said:</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-16a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T05:05:30.363+09:00">“The Book of Songs states:</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-16a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T05:05:37.766+09:00">Like bone carved and polished,</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-16a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T05:05:43.914+09:00">Like jade cut and ground.19</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-16a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T05:05:48.44+09:00">Is this not what you have in mind?”</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-16a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T05:05:58.786+09:00">The Master said:</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-16a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T05:06:06.606+09:00"> “Zigong,</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-16a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T05:06:15.232+09:00">it is only with thelikes of you then that I can discuss the Songs!</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-17a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T05:06:17.44+09:00">Onthe basis of what has been said, you know what isyet to come.”</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-17a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T05:06:39.388+09:00">The Master said:</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-17a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T05:06:48.519+09:00">“Don’t worry about not beingacknowledged by others;</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_001-17a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2023-10-19T05:06:49.69+09:00">worry about failing toacknowledge them.”</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_005-14a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-01-25T07:48:04.477+09:00">Zigong said, “I do not want others to impose on me,</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_005-14a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-01-25T07:11:04.419+09:00">nor do I want to impose on others.”</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_005-14a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-01-25T07:35:49.125+09:00">Confucius　replied,</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_005-14a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-01-25T07:11:17.178+09:00">“Zigong,</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_005-15a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-01-25T07:11:19.375+09:00"> this is quite beyond your reach.”</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_002-18a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-03-09T05:08:59.304+09:00">The Master said:</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_002-18a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-03-09T05:09:08.725+09:00">“Zilu,35</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_002-18a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-03-09T07:39:54.96+09:00">shall I teach you what wisdom (zhi ) means?”</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_002-18a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-03-09T06:22:14.37+09:00">To know (zhi ) what you know</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_002-18a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-03-09T05:09:31.975+09:00">and know what you do not know</seg><seg corresp="#KR1h0004_tls_002-19a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-03-09T06:20:39.043+09:00">—this then is wisdom.”36</seg></p></div></body></text></TEI>